Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

AS TO COUNT 1:   
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 9 YEARS and 6 MONTHS, consecutive to COUNT 2 and to any other sentence, the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 5 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 4 YEARS and 6 MONTHS.

AS TO COUNT 2:   
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 4 YEARS, consecutive to COUNT 1 and to any other sentence, the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 2 YEARS.

Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program. 
Court orders: 
Provide DNA sample (unless previously submitted) and pay surcharge.
Court costs, fines, surcharges and be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b). If not paid in full at the end of the initial confinement the remaining balance will be entered as a civil judgment. 

As to COUNT 2: Court prohibits contact with Joshua B. (4/27/1981) and Javod P (2/25/1986)

As to COUNT 1 and COUNT 2 Court orders the terms of Extended Supervision as follows: 
-	Absolute Sobriety, no alcohol;
-	Defendant NOT to possess or use any controlled substances unless by valid prescription. 
-	Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment and successfully complete recommended treatment including drug and alcohol testing. 
-	No possession of any firearm or weapon, ammunition;
-	No use or possession of illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-	No contact with Joshua B. or Javod P. 
-	Defendant may not possess more than $200.00 in cash at any time;
-	Successfully complete a Parenting Class;
-	Successfully complete a Cognitive Behavior Program.
-	Seek and maintain full time work, school or a combination of both;

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession; Voting
Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
